Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.24,0:23:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and what could my relationship with christ be to really enhance my life well we differentiate it\Nbetween the and the purpose of the life of jesus christ and salvation and i think that's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.58,0:23:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,why the x then theOkay soетр suprumanity's right the purpose of christ is to change the\Nlife of buddha as compared to christ yes jesus christ represents salvation and what do
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.02,0:23:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that mean salvation means reaching heaven heaven the celestial realms unconditional\Nlove at 5 40. what did jesus christ say is to learn to love and when you love when love
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.61,0:23:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is your orientation upon the physical death the spirit goes to the celestial realms called\Nheaven on south north carolina christianity is a work of prabhin mantras we really like
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.63,0:23:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that because we always come up with great ideas to deal with tens of thousands of questions\Nand the same as Lotus Land Buddhism,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.79,0:23:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you lead a good life and therefore land in the celestial realm.\NThe purpose of Buddha is to teach enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.59,0:24:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beyond the celestial realms.\NSo, Lotus Land Buddhism in Christianity is practical.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.84,0:24:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It says the negativity of life in this world is so extreme,\Nthe likelihood of getting past the gravity of that negativity is slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.84,0:24:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people ever become enlightened from this domain.\NPractically never.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.52,0:24:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The gravity of negativity here is profound, see?\NThe energy field, it's like the fog, it's so heavy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.52,0:24:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To see the sun is very rare.\NBut if you lead a good life, then with Jesus Christ as your savior,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.93,0:24:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so he's your guru, he's your teacher.\NJesus Christ said to forgive rather than, you know, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.44,0:24:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then upon death you go to the celestial realm.\NFrom the celestial realm, which is the same as Lotus Land,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.44,0:24:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotus Land Buddhism, from there the gravity is much less,\Nand from there you can go on to higher levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.24,0:25:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always imagined that what we consider\Nthe most advanced level of consciousness in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.68,0:25:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is kindergarten in another realm.\NWell, when you calibrate that archangels are 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.87,0:25:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole idea of bearing punishment\Nfor sin is not...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.87,0:25:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think that has to do with punishment.\NRight. Great. Thank you much.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.87,0:25:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I have a hug?\NYeah. Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.65,0:25:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that okay? Am I on?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.20,0:26:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you. Yes.\NYes, I just want to thank you so very much
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.48,0:26:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for the very powerful work that you've done today\Nand have been doing for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.48,0:26:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a person of color, it's disconcerting to me\Nto look at the planet and to see the level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.48,0:26:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of the countries of third world peoples being so low.\NI know you said there's no cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.48,0:26:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the answer to that?\NIt's karmic. It's karmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.48,0:26:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic.\NIs this historical? Is this always been true?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.48,0:26:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is this something that's karmic that is...\NWell, I only did it for current world, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.48,0:26:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see, how can a child be born\Nwith AIDS, born to starvation,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.48,0:26:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and then is going to be chopped up\Nby a warlord of a neighboring tribe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.48,0:26:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,into pieces while it's still living?\NI mean, how can it be, see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.92,0:27:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,without the fact that this being had a karmic indebtedness\Nof having done that to others,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.92,0:27:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and now one does it through experiencing?\NI see no way to rationalize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.01,0:27:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget that mankind has massacred mankind throughout history.\NSo let's take the Vikings that came over
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.27,0:27:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and slaughtered people needlessly,\Ncivilians and children alike,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.27,0:27:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,just like is being done in Chesna or something like now.\NSo when you blow up 300 innocent children,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.27,0:27:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how are you going to undo that karma?\NHow are you going to undo it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.10,0:27:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to have an opportunity\Nto know what it is to get blown up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.32,0:27:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with no... blindsided like that.\NHow can you undo the karma? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.68,0:27:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So there has to be some place,\Nthere has to be some place to undo the karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you know?\NOtherwise you'd be condemned to hell forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.14,0:27:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So there must be some way to undo it.\NAnd that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.84,0:27:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got nothing to do with color.\NI just happened to be incidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.84,0:28:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIt's got nothing to do with color.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.94,0:28:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It has nothing to do with color.\NNo, I think color people are lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.94,0:28:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I always admire them.\NHave you ever been colored in your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.29,0:28:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I have. Yes, indeed.\NAnd you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.29,0:28:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the acceptance of the emotional side.\NSee, when you're brought up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.29,0:28:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,strictly white Anglo-Saxon,\Nyou're not supposed to have feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.29,0:28:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Very abstract.\NSo your mother says to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.29,0:28:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in my own life, you know,\NI went to the whitewash in the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.29,0:28:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, geez, Ma,\NI wanted to play ball with the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.29,0:28:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, wipe that look off your face, young man.\NYou weren't allowed to have feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.29,0:28:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The comfort of being able to have feelings\Nis what I enjoyed about it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.03,0:28:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.05,0:29:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times.\NThey've already asked all my questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.80,0:29:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a certain memory and viewpoint\Nbeing white's a drag.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.22,0:29:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So stiff and formal.\NGive me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.54,0:29:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.88,0:29:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm using muscle testing\Nto test the efficacy of a marketing campaign
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.20,0:29:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or the best direction\Nto make my business,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.20,0:29:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,how do I do that without explicitly asking\Nfor a future event,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.43,0:29:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge about a future event?\NTo ask something, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.54,0:29:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of the answer\Nis based on the integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.80,0:30:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of the intention of the question.\NAnd self-benefit is below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.83,0:30:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you ask is in the name of the highest good.\NIn the name of the highest good,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.76,0:30:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you ask that my company develop this product,\Nemploy this person,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.76,0:30:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,go in this direction,\Nwould serve the highest good
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.85,0:30:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because the highest good serves everybody,\Nthe customer, the purchaser,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.85,0:30:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the salesman, the manufacturer,\Nthe owner, the licensor,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.62,0:30:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good.\NSo when we ask anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.16,0:30:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we ask in the name of the highest good.\NWhen we get an invitation to speak someplace,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.16,0:30:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we say, these people are integrals.\NYes, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.16,0:30:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Would it serve the highest good\Nto accept speaking in Dayton?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.16,0:30:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we get a yes.\NSo if we got a no, we wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.32,0:30:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The only reason we're here is we got that\Nit serves the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.32,0:30:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So it has nothing to do with personal preference,\Nnothing to do with gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.32,0:31:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can inquire about your company\Nand say it serves the highest good
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.32,0:31:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because who are you serving?\NAre you serving employees?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.32,0:31:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serving the owners?\NAfter all, you have a right to profit
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.32,0:31:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from your own endeavor, too, isn't it?\NYou're not negated.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.32,0:31:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that you want to bypass pure selfishness.\NSo it serves the highest good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.32,0:31:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I usually ask everything in terms of the highest good.\NIt serves the highest good to speak in Dayton
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.32,0:31:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or not to speak in Dayton.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.68,0:31:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it serves the highest good,\Nso that's why we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.60,0:31:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.74,0:31:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.16,0:31:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NGood question.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.60,0:31:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to have a drink of Diet Pepsi.\NTurn off that camera for one instant
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.60,0:31:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,while I have a drink of Diet Pepsi.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.60,0:31:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No looking.\NNo, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.60,0:31:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NUh-uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.60,0:32:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYou've spoken of karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.24,0:32:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't see it as punishment.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.24,0:32:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Just consequence.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.75,0:32:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's non-moralistic, you know.\NIt's automatic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.75,0:32:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Morality is one way to look at it,\Nbut it is just the consequences of your own actions,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.99,0:32:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, and your own intentions.\NSo it can be the same action.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.02,0:32:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,action, but the intention makes it completely different. You know, when that\Nwarrior and I killed each other, we had the same intention. I did it for God, he
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.46,0:32:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,did it for God, and we served each other. Warriors, warriors honor each other. When\Nthe war is over, the first people who shake hands and salute the other are the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.69,0:33:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,warriors. The men at Armistice sign the officers, the men of each side, salute\Neach other. They salute each other's honor because each one did it for the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.78,0:33:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,honor of serving God and country, the king, whatever. Yeah, so war is not what it\Nlooks like on the surface. Many hidden aspects to war are the undoing of negative
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.11,0:33:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,karma, crossing over below 200 to above 200, valor, service, honor, many things\Ninvolved in war. A simple person, you know, just says all war is bad. Yeah, right, you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.61,0:33:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be alive if it weren't for war.\NNone of you had freedom if it weren't for war. So, okay, you'd all be dead. If it weren't for war, you wouldn't be alive. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.29,0:34:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is for many people in St. Louis. I'm carrying you back. I got a hug from St. Louis. That's neat.\NI wonder if you have a foundation in what it does. I mean, do you have, do you have some sort of a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.50,0:34:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,foundation?\NOr do you just, are you just speaking on a speaking tour? Or do you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.32,0:34:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,foundation? Some kind of a foundation? Oh, we have a nonprofit research\Ninstitute, yes, Institute for Spiritual Studies, yes. Oh, that's all? We publish all the books. So that you, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.70,0:34:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,basically what you do. I mean you don't... We write, we do research, we publish books,\Nwe teach, we give lectures, yes. I was a little bit disturbed by the answer to the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.74,0:34:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,question of the previous lady that asked about Africa and the, your\Nyour idea of the karma of a young baby that suffered all the things that you said?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.12,0:34:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAre you blaming the baby for a prior life?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.12,0:34:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about karma. How are you going to understand the negative karma?\NSo, in other words, it's the baby's fault that it's being chopped up?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.12,0:35:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Not fault. No, you're interjecting. I didn't say anything about fault.\NYou just said fault. I didn't say anything about fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.12,0:35:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm trying to understand what you said.\NI said karma. Karma is, by your own intention, you become this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.12,0:35:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of this...\NWell, that's a way of separating yourself from that fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.18,0:35:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You create a wave.\NIsn't it convenient to separate yourself from the suffering in that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.18,0:35:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, to just say, oh, that's happening over there. I'm not involved in that.\NWhose karma is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.86,0:35:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about karma. I don't quite understand. I mean, I wouldn't just accept...\NDid you come out of nothingness? How did you arise as who you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.86,0:35:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it necessarily that I pick up something?\NIs it some kind of karma? That's like heliotropism is a definition of something that doesn't tell me anything. It's just a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.86,0:35:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you explain your own existence?\NI don't have to. Why would I have to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.50,0:35:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you asking any question right now?\NI'm here right now celebrating it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.50,0:36:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You doubt it already. Otherwise, you wouldn't be asking me a question.\NYou would be certain about the nature of your own existence and its source, and it answers its own questions, and you have no question.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.50,0:36:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, I'm happy to be here dancing with you.\NBut I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.50,0:36:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The worst thing is you don't understand the concept of karma.\NNo, you haven't explained it to me, is what I'm saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.50,0:36:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you'd have to be a student. You know, it takes a little while to understand karma.\NEverything is the consequence of...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.88,0:36:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's like heliotropism. You have to get a little bit...\NNo, no, no. You're trying to ridicule it. Instead, you're not asking a question. You're coming up to ridicule me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.88,0:36:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.\NIf you ask a question, I'll teach you what karma is.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.88,0:36:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NKarma is an ancient knowingness from the ancient East.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.88,0:36:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's verifiable through calibrating levels of consciousness.\NIt's not commonly accepted in the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.71,0:37:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it is commonly accepted in the Western world in a different way.\NThat when you leave this physicality, you will suffer the consequences of your decisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.90,0:37:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Your spiritual decisions in this lifetime will decide whether you go to heaven or hell.\NThat's what Jesus Christ said.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.90,0:37:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Jesus Christ and the Buddha and Krishna and all the great avatars...\NWhat would you do if you found yourself in hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.90,0:37:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been in hell.\NWhat did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.90,0:37:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't advise it. I asked for God to get me out of it.\NWell, you changed it, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.90,0:37:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't change it.\NSo I think that that might be what we might want to do for those children in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.90,0:37:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Change hell?\NChange their situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.90,0:37:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, go ahead and change it.\NWell, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.90,0:37:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for you.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.90,0:37:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm worried about it.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.25,0:37:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She says, I wonder if you have to soak your arm at night.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.63,0:37:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Arianne Pacey still alive, or is she dead?\NIs what?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.94,0:37:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne Pacey.\NArianne Pacey?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.94,0:37:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what she's saying.\NArianne Pacey.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.07,0:37:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne?\NArianne Pacey.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.07,0:37:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what she's saying.\NWe don't hear she.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.07,0:37:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,She's my best friend's daughter.\NShe's been missing since, for four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.07,0:38:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what she's saying.\NArianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.07,0:38:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne?\NArianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.07,0:38:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne?\NArianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.07,0:38:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne?\NArianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.07,0:38:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne?\NArianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.07,0:38:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne?\NArianne, Arianne, Arianne, Arianne, Arianne.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.07,0:38:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say Arianne?\NArianne?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.26,0:38:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Arianne, Arianne, Arianne, Arianne, Arianne.\NArianne, Arianne, Arianne, Arianne, Arianne.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.50,0:38:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been missing for four years.\NYeah, I couldn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.63,0:38:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't know?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.63,0:38:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Any way I can find out?\NWhat do you need to know for?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.63,0:38:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It would ease my friend's suffering.\NOh, then it's your friend's problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.63,0:38:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you making it yours?\NIt would ease my suffering to ease hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.63,0:38:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're joining in sort of an identification with the situation, huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.95,0:38:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sympathy.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.95,0:38:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.95,0:39:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah okay well we'll talk to you later that's a personal question I don't know\Nif I permission to answer you see I'm not gonna do that in public thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.44,0:39:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,about some of the things that you said today yes working on my own\Nunderstanding of all coming from the same nothingness and the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.27,0:39:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,about what has then what is the meaning of the experience of personal choice and\Nso I was looking at the ideas that you talked about of all of all experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.89,0:39:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything coming from nothingness the movements whatever and at the same time\Nthe possibility of having choice and where there's the personal it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.23,0:39:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning of being an individual fit into that structure of all coming from\Nnothingness your question doesn't make sense it's a
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.71,0:39:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,semanticist\Nbut it's not a question what is the question I'm working on the expert what
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.20,0:40:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the meaning of the experience of being an individual what is the meaning\Nof experience you mean in a generic sense or you personally for me personally
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.02,0:40:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the only person I can invest that seems to be the only thing\Nthat I can address yeah so what is the question and then I'm thinking and also
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.04,0:40:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to understand the idea of all being part of coming from the same\Nnothingness and all coming from I didn't say we come from nothingness I didn't say
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.92,0:40:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm sorry I said thoughts arise from nothing it's thought arises from\Nnothing okay I didn't say we arise from nothingness that's not a possibility we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.03,0:40:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,arise from allness but again the same is it the same allness the infinite allness\Nis by definition allness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.62,0:40:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,allness context what you know each of us at the same time is different half it\Nhas different experiences yes at least in our awareness that's correct have in
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.11,0:41:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,our awareness we have different experiences I'm trying to correlate\Ndifferences which I interpret as separation but at experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.15,0:41:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,separation yeah yeah experience is a separation when I know when I at least\Nintellectually understand that there is no separation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.13,0:41:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah and I'm trying to make sure you're asking me from an ontologic level I\Nbelieve that I understand the sense of the meaning of that word yeah the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.74,0:41:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,significance of beingness itself in existence is that what you're asking in\Nthe context of the difference between being that being sensed individually
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.64,0:41:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this or being that I sent being senses being individual being this or being\Nthat then is up to personal choice and that comes about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.04,0:42:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of divine ordinance and yet we're all part of the same diviner or not\Nthe same allness divine ordinance calibrates at an infinite level of course yes and
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.53,0:42:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,yours probably doesn't calibrate over a thousand right sure yeah and so it's like\Nwe're all reflections of the diamond you know it's like each one of us is a reflection of the
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.98,0:42:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,same primordial truth that is the essence of all of us yes a dimension of\Nall a different dimension of the same thing thank you each one of us is a
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.60,0:43:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,reflection of the diamond you know why it should be I don't know that's divine\Nwill divine will that it should be so thank you I like divine ordinance you can
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.72,0:43:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,just blame it all on God and you're done with it\Nmy question is about karma yeah no I while you were speaking you expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.80,0:43:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it quite a knowledge of your past lifetimes and I've wondering how\Nimportant you feel it is or how helpful it would be for a person to be aware of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.18,0:43:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,some of their past karma and if so how do you figure out what\Nwhat they might have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.33,0:43:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma in past lifetimes is a whole lecture in and of itself.\NIt's a pretty advanced, sophisticated level.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.21,0:43:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,At a certain level of consciousness,\Nsuddenly one becomes aware that there's not
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.57,0:44:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,individual separate lives.\NThere's only one life with various incarnations.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.21,0:44:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And you remember the incarnations\Nbecause each one of them had usually
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.50,0:44:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,had a very profound and significant spiritual lesson\Nat the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.67,0:44:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why you remember them very specifically.\NYou remember them very specifically, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.86,0:44:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And also, before that happens, very often one intuits it.\NAlmost like you intuit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.58,0:44:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I must have been so-and-so\Nbecause of this and that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.88,0:44:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, there's various ways of investigating it.\NYou can go into past life research.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.52,0:44:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a very simple technique of self-hypnosis,\Nwhich I could teach you, in which you go down
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.16,0:44:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and down.\NAnd then you ask the question, and you get in the elevator,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.30,0:44:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get off the 10th floor.\NAnd the experience that you're asking for reruns.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.22,0:45:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a memory.\NYou re-experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.30,0:45:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's past life recall.\NThere is various technicians of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.90,0:45:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,various hypnotists and various therapists\Nwho specialize in past life recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.96,0:45:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's very helpful to overcome\Na very specific problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.00,0:45:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A very specific symptom.\NA very specific symptom.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.35,0:45:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you recall that, it will relieve the symptom.\NUsually a forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.62,0:45:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually a forgiveness.\NI had to forgive myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.68,0:45:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're interested in past life,\Nit explains karmically perhaps why
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.15,0:45:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,certain things are happening.\NI use the example.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.58,0:46:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this sitting here?\NI use the example of going through surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.56,0:46:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Without anesthesia.\NAnd one time I was going through surgery without anesthesia
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.20,0:46:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,for an inguinal hernia.\NAnd the pain was excruciating.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.54,0:46:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of this excruciating pain,\NI recalled the warrior that I speared right through the groin.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.30,0:46:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I did not do the coup de grace.\NI did not relieve his agony by cutting his throat or killing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.31,0:46:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,him.\NI left him to die of his wounds and agony, which takes weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.08,0:46:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The guilt of that lasted all these lifetimes.\NAll these lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.22,0:46:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I undid the karmic pain and agony\Nof what I subjected him to through moral cowardice
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.22,0:46:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I didn't kill him.\NThe warrior owes the other warrior
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.98,0:46:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the honor of handing him the gun with a single bullet\Nin if he wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.80,0:47:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's up to the warrior to decide.\NSo it was my failure of moral courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.30,0:47:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have executed the coup de grace out\Nof saluting his honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.29,0:47:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I punished myself by going through exactly what\Nhe experienced, agony.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.36,0:47:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That began to run in the middle of surgery.\NI just saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.16,0:47:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew what I'd done.\NI apologized to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.47,0:47:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I'm sorry that I lacked the moral courage.\NThe coup de grace, which is, you wouldn't understand probably
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.01,0:47:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,as a woman, but as a man, coup de grace\Nis what I owe my fellow warrior as a warrior.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.23,0:47:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.26,0:47:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter who you're fighting for.\NI, as a warrior, or you as a warrior, got courtesy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.93,0:47:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I failed him.\NSo that guilt lasted all these lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.62,0:47:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I had a chance to undo it.\NSo you see, it might be something specific like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.64,0:47:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a certain symptom in your stomach,\Nlet's say, in which past life recall
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.50,0:48:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,might be useful in relieving it.\NUsually, it's a forgiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.26,0:48:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, it's a forgiveness.\NSo I had to forgive myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.12,0:48:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to forgive myself for having failed him.\NAnd I apologized to his spirit that I failed you, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.53,0:48:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I still feel sadness about it.\NYeah, I do, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.88,0:48:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am.\NThis is one of our girls that volunteered to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.18,0:48:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.00,0:48:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.50,0:48:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait, wait, wait, wait.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.01,0:48:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wait.\NOh, she wants a hug, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.76,0:48:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the girls that helped put this all on.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.28,0:48:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you so much, sweetheart, for putting this on.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.73,0:49:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,My question of the two United States\Npresidential candidates, George Bush and John Kerry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.41,0:49:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that the late 1800s?\NThe current election, 2004.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.65,0:49:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,On a scale of 1 to 1,000, a logarithmic scale of 1\Nto 1,000, what are the individual calibrations
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.65,0:49:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,of those two?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.77,0:49:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the individual calibrations of those two\Npresidential candidates?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.65,0:49:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll leave it to you to find out, sir.\NI will teach you kinesiology, and you can do your own research.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.99,0:49:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do that for the common good.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.96,0:49:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,May the best man win.\NIs being president good karma or bad karma?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.55,0:49:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell me.\NI would consider it bad karma for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.91,0:49:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but for somebody else, it might be good karma.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.69,0:49:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,About five years ago, my energy was released.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.09,0:49:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,About five years ago.\NAbout five years ago, my energy was released.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.79,0:49:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?\NMy kundalini energy was released,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.63,0:50:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn't realize what had happened.\NAnd through a kinesiologist in Atlanta,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.35,0:50:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,she put me in touch with some masters.\NI feel the energy in my body 24 hours a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.63,0:50:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes it's very painful.\NI see things I don't understand, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.70,0:50:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of at the end of things.\NI've read your books.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.82,0:50:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd they answer a lot of questions for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.26,0:50:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know you don't see people individually anymore,\Nbut I didn't know if you can give me any kind of guidance
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.94,0:50:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what I might do now.\NWhy are you calling it kundalini energy to begin with?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.40,0:50:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's what everybody has told me that it is.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.94,0:50:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that's what everyone has told me.\NWho's what everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.00,0:50:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiots.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.09,0:50:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'd want to give her some disease she doesn't have,\Nlike wild crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.86,0:50:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?\NWhat's the kundalini energy?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.30,0:51:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the energy rises and falls in my body a lot.\NBut then when during the day or, well, 24 hours a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.54,0:51:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't sleep very much.\NI feel it pull and tug in my body
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.72,0:51:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and go through different things, like it's trying to clear things.\NOh, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.08,0:51:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I feel like it's.\NI see what you're saying, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.88,0:51:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a therapist that you're working on with this, balancing\Nenergy, or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.96,0:51:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've worked with a couple of, through the kinesiologist,\NI've worked with a couple of masters from Malaysia.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.80,0:51:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm a Methodist.\NAnd I don't have very much residence
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.12,0:51:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,for that part of what they're telling me.\NSo I don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.34,0:51:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You've seen a psychiatrist, too?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.92,0:51:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.\NYou should see one.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.46,0:51:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NYeah, each person in society has a function, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.24,0:51:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a time you need a dentist,\Ntime you need a psychiatrist, time you need a priest,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.88,0:51:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,time you need somebody to bury you, see?\NSo the talents, whatever they can offer, each one offers.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.60,0:52:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A piece of the puzzle, and then it sort of fits together.\NYou know, I got something with psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.46,0:52:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I got something from introspection.\NI got something from university.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.42,0:52:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I got something from the great books of the Western world.\NI got something from all those things, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.72,0:52:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a mosaic.\NSo you put together what you can learn from each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.46,0:52:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the answer seems to come out of the composite.\NYou don't have enough information yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.89,0:52:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you're saying.\NI don't have the information to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.35,0:52:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what's going on with me.\NI guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.83,0:52:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo you need some more.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.15,0:52:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The masters tell me the answer is within myself,\Nthat I should meditate.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.57,0:52:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, anybody can tell you that.\NI can tell you that for 5 and 1 half cents, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.73,0:52:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.73,0:52:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be a nickel.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.39,0:52:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NFrom what you're telling me, these random energies that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.82,0:52:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,are not leveled out.\NI would ask a psychiatrist what he thinks of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.46,0:52:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NAnd you will just consult masters on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.12,0:52:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and other wild and crazy things, you know.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.63,0:53:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That, you know, I would consult somebody professionally\Ntrained also, who's aware of human brain physiology
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.29,0:53:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and emotions and acupuncture systems and all,\Nand can put it together for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.19,0:53:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have it together, right?\NYou don't have it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.45,0:53:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,See, there's something missing from your puzzle.\NWell, they told me I've had a lot of trauma and accidents
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.79,0:53:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and things.\NYeah, but those are generalities, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.11,0:53:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are generalities.\NLet me ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.59,0:53:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry to ask personal questions,\Nbut that was the only way I got to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.71,0:53:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but that's.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.81,0:53:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.79,0:53:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.79,0:53:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIf you're missing in the answer, then, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.33,0:53:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you got to search for somebody who can add to the puzzle.\NWhen you get the whole puzzle together,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.89,0:53:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,then it sort of makes sense.\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.11,0:53:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.27,0:53:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NUh-huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.83,0:53:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very grateful for you and Susan and the whole staff.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.69,0:53:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at your last seminar and said I just love the love.\NI've read your three books, and I'm just very grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.63,0:54:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a, you made a statement that I, maybe you could\Nclarify, you can't transcend until you master it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.95,0:54:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd my question is, if I'm wanting to move toward 500 and 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.31,0:54:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,do I read books?\NDo I ponder that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.57,0:54:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do I master the intellect in some way, which seems a little harder to do?\NOh, I see what you're saying, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.33,0:54:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's a matter of intention.\NSo let's say that intention will bypass many things.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.11,0:54:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In many ways, it's easier to jump from the 300s to the 500s\Nthan it is to go all the way through the 400s, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.99,0:54:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you realize that the Newtonian paradigm is not\Nthe ultimate reality, you've already taken a giant leap over the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.31,0:54:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NOnce you realize that 500 is unconditional love, 500 is love, 540
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.93,0:55:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is unconditional love, you say, well, what groups teach unconditional love?\NAnd what are the premises that get them there?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.21,0:55:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the 12th century.\N12-step groups are probably the best demonstration of 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.79,0:55:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best demonstration of 600 or so is miracles groups.\NI say, if you really want to evolve spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.69,0:55:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I would practice the 12 steps and do miracles, the Course in Miracles.\NAnd if you do that wholeheartedly, you'll automatically be that, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.48,0:55:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds wonderful.\NWell, it means that if you have any grievance, the 10th step,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.24,0:55:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you apologize for having to do that.\NYou apologize for having any grievance or having misspoken yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.78,0:55:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You pray through the 11th step through meditation,\Nconsciousness, awareness of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.41,0:55:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You become responsible to your human, everybody around you,\Nby trying to be as loving and forgiving as you can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.85,0:55:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And automatically, you're in the 500s, because that's\Nwhat the people in the 500s are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.31,0:56:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They're trying to be aware of the sacredness of all of life.\NThey're trying to be of goodwill towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.19,0:56:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you see a little black beetle in an alley,\Nand he's lying on his back, you can't help but take a twig
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.23,0:56:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and help him to go over, see?\NYour intellect says, that's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.49,0:56:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But your heart says, if your heart,\Nif you walk by this black beetle, and he's flapping like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.01,0:56:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's helpless, you get hit with guilt.\NI've tried it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.82,0:56:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't get more than five paces.\NYou say, your intellect says, it's only about a bug,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.64,0:56:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's on its way out, and it doesn't mean anything anyway.\NBut somehow, guilt tugs at you that you have failed its appeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.98,0:56:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So then, your heart pulls you back,\Nand you turn the beetle over.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.24,0:56:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you do that, your intellect says, that's ridiculous.\NBut now, you feel happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.64,0:56:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you can't bypass the beetle anymore,\Nthen you know you're over 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.58,0:56:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,May I have a hug?\NYeah, you can have a hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.94,0:57:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWell, I'll make you a hug.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.70,0:57:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a member of the Black Beetle League.\NI like the sport jacket, too, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.21,0:57:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we will no longer bypass black beetles\Nwith their little arms waving in the wind, we'll say.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.29,0:57:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Help, help, help, give me a twig, and say, oh, thank you,\Nthank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.91,0:57:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Little black beetles praying, oh, help me, God, help me, God.\NHelp, help, help, help.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.01,0:57:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And along comes the twig.\NThank you, Dr. Harkins, for coming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.28,0:57:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And bless you for doing it.\NYou mentioned in 1987 that the Harmonic Concordance raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.84,0:57:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,No, at the time of the Harmonic Concordance.\NAt the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.52,0:57:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Not caused by it.\NThe mankind's consciousness raised over the 200 mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.60,0:57:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, from 190 to 205, yes.\NMy question is, can the 15% at the top
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.40,0:58:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,of the apex of the pyramid come together\Nwith a unified effort of loving kindness, world peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.18,0:58:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.28,0:58:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Or one consciousness, and effect a quantum leap\Nthat we might see peace in our time?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.37,0:58:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's too mechanistic of you.\NYou're looking at it from causality,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.49,0:58:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but this causing it that.\NNo, it's that the 15% by their buoyancy tends
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.71,0:58:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to pull up the whole field by their buoyancy, by what they are\Nand not what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.79,0:58:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So they couldn't get together.\NThey don't know who each other is, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.47,0:58:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But the intention, you see, the intention of over 200\Nis integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.70,0:58:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What's common to over 200 is truth and integrity.\NWhat's common to below 200 is what I feel and what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.60,0:58:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And over 200, they teach you what you feel and what you want\Nis nice, but it's really irrelevant to the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.66,0:59:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,answer for mankind, you see?\NSo over 200, you mean to sacrifice personal selfishness,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.54,0:59:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and under 200, personal selfishness\Nis supposed to be given dominance, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.26,0:59:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So the combined intention is like a buoyancy\Nthat pulls up the whole field by what it is, not what it does,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.46,0:59:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of what it is.\NJust be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.34,0:59:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So karma is like a cork, like a cork.\NAnd every choice, so I didn't really
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.40,0:59:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,finish the lecture today.\NI said, you know, the infinite field of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.59,0:59:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is like a giant electromagnetic field.\NEach one of us is born karmically
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.69,0:59:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,like a little magnetized particle.\NAnd we will automatically go into the field
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.13,0:59:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,as a consequence of that which we are.\NThat which you are automatically determines
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.95,0:59:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,where you go in the field.\NThe field is infinitely powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.19,0:59:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're shaped like this, you go there.\NIf you're shaped like this, you go there, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.63,1:00:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,As a consequence of the field.\NSo that which you have become through your own intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.01,1:00:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by your own choice.\NBy your own sin, determines where you will go.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.73,1:00:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're like a cork.\NSo a cork that says yes, yes to love floats high.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.69,1:00:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And one that rebukes love, says love is a weakness\Nand it's despicable, and hatred is better,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.33,1:00:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,will sink to the bottom, see?\NAs a consequence of that which they are.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.11,1:00:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Not as a consequence of a punitive god.\NNot as a consequence of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.51,1:00:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a punitive god is just a depiction of duality projected\Non to causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.64,1:00:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a depiction of God, you know?\NAre we done?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.98,1:00:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, OK.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.36,1:00:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NOh, that line is gone, OK?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.93,1:00:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAfternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.99,1:01:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is a personal one, physically,\Nwhich would hopefully benefit the rest of mankind
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.28,1:01:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in its unfolding.\NFor years I've been struggling with some low back pain, which
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.60,1:01:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe is due to a disruption of the second chakra.\NAnd issues there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.24,1:01:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the second chakra?\NWell, it's the energy center around the sacrum.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.68,1:01:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, yeah.\NI suppose this being asks your presence
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.52,1:01:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to help assist dislodge that disruption\Nand allow for a free flow of energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.84,1:01:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's blocking it?\NI believe the issues of the second chakra
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.73,1:01:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to be of sexual energy and its expression into the world.\NAnd so for me, that's one of the issues that I've been wrestling
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.99,1:01:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with in proper expression of these energies\Nin a creative way that isn't a.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.87,1:01:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you try breathing it up.\NBreathe it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.83,1:01:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathe it up.\NBreathe it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.83,1:01:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathe it up.\NPicture it as an energy flowing up the chakra system.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.75,1:02:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And breathe it out of that chakra.\NAnd breathe it up to the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.34,1:02:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Breathe it up to the heart.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.52,1:02:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like a slap in the head instead of a hug today, please.\NHe would like a what?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.06,1:02:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,A slap in the head.\NI can't hear him.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.60,1:02:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted a slap in the head instead of a hug.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.24,1:02:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.08,1:02:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.36,1:02:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.\NIt's because he's young.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.50,1:02:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When you get older, you won't have to complain.\NAge will cure it, my boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.27,1:02:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How come there's, um, I find myself on this list,\Nboth at the bottom and at the top,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.27,1:02:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I realize that most of the calibrations\Nthat you give, you give one number.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.25,1:02:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that work?\NHow does what work?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.55,1:03:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm here, and there, and there, and there, and there.\NOh, no, those are just passing emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.33,1:03:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.\NYour lifestyle, what you stand for,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.69,1:03:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,your prevailing attitude towards life\Nwill tell you where you are in the field there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.14,1:03:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Prevailing, prevailing, you know, moment to moment.\NThose are just passing emotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.76,1:03:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.89,1:03:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NDedicate your life to what you live by.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.32,1:03:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Tells you where you are, you know?\NIf your life is dedicated to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.00,1:03:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,getting even with somebody, then you\Nknow you're dedicated to hatred, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.88,1:03:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd so, you know, you can tell by what the dedication
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.54,1:03:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of your life is to, you know?\NYeah, boy, that gives me hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.96,1:03:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah, there's hope for you, or you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.22,1:03:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't be up here asking a question.\NHa, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.20,1:03:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm up here.\NYeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.58,1:03:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very angry.\NYou wouldn't be up asking.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.40,1:03:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be up asking a question\Nif you weren't aligned with self-improvement
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.94,1:04:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and transcending wherever you're at, you know?\NI don't have a question.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.48,1:04:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted a moment of your attention.\NYeah, thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.02,1:04:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.54,1:04:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How much I appreciate your wisdom, your wit, humor.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.62,1:04:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you share it.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.46,1:04:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a blessing just to have you ask me that.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.24,1:04:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to say thanks for everything.\NI just wanted to get a hug.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.32,1:04:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, indeed.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.00,1:04:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fine indeed, yeah?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.80,1:04:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NGod bless you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.54,1:04:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NGod bless you.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.74,1:04:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,See how many beautiful people come up.\NWoof.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.69,1:04:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.69,1:04:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins, would you please comment\Non the calibration of some of the Sufi masters, such as Rumi?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.61,1:04:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you them specifically,\Nbecause I'm not a Sufi student.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.57,1:04:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I remember Rumi is high, yes, high.\NOver 600 or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.67,1:04:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember him.\NBut I'm not into Sufi masters much.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.87,1:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't have time to study such a thing.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.52,1:05:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NUnfortunately.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.52,1:05:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.\NI don't know what I wasted my life on.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.31,1:05:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There's so many things I haven't had time to study yet.\NI don't know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.31,1:05:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.18,1:05:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This Sufi is your head at the back.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.09,1:05:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYou'll just have to come back and do it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.55,1:05:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no, no.\NNever say no, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.13,1:05:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTake the date and there's still time.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.46,1:05:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't know if I can do that.\NBut I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.16,1:05:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I spent so many years doing psychiatry,\Nthat wasn't a problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.54,1:05:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Hawkins.\NFirst of all, I'd like to give thanks to you
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.78,1:05:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,for coming here today and sharing your knowledge and wisdom.\NIt definitely has raised my level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.04,1:05:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is, you mentioned that music\Nhas a calibration of 700.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.58,1:05:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular music, yes.\NMy question is, have you ever done any calibration on,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.76,1:06:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say, quote, quote, rap music or?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.11,1:06:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And what has that?\NWe did a lot of music.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.67,1:06:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We did a lot of music.\NIn the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.17,1:06:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The book that we're going to publish.\NWe did many famous musicians, from Rachmaninoff to Beethoven.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.29,1:06:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We did recent pop artists, operas.\NWe did Count Basie, people like that, basic jazz people.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.83,1:06:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Current rap does not calibrate very high, gutter rap,\Ncalling women whores.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.72,1:06:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Kicking pregnant ladies in the belly does not calibrate very high.\NSo did you actually do any calibration on that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.34,1:06:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we did.\NAnd they're quite low.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.51,1:07:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, each level of society has its own music.\NAnd from the top to the bottom, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.18,1:07:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And to express such negativity so grossly calibrates low.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.32,1:07:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it glamorizes.\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.72,1:07:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It glamorizes violence.\NAbsolutely.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.14,1:07:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibers.\NIt isn't so much what's alluded to is the glamorization of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.44,1:07:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That you should be this way, you'll be hip, you'll be a star.\NIt's the seduction of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.64,1:07:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the seduction of the glamorization of negativity\Nis where the error is.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.78,1:07:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've seen some rap musicians come on and say, correctly,\Nthat they came out of poverty into, you know, wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.82,1:07:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This way.\NAnd I think, OK, now that you've got that,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.00,1:07:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,now you should become a pattern for identification\Nfor what is beyond just money gain, you know, and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.40,1:07:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So I understand that they're saying\Nthis is a way out of the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.92,1:08:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I appreciate that, that that's true.\NIn your final analysis, has there
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.50,1:08:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,been a correlation between the negativity of the rap\Nand the low consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.86,1:08:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NLow consciousness, let's say, of the African-American community?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.86,1:08:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have to do with African-American.\NIt has to do with the glorification of that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.60,1:08:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which is not integrous.\NYou see, the strong masculine honors women.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.31,1:08:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The weak masculine despises women.\NThe weak masculine fears women and despises them, denigrates
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.71,1:08:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,them, calls them whores, or captivates them,\Nand keeps them subjugated without the right
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.36,1:08:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to own property or vote, et cetera.\NThe strong masculine loves women and honors them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.32,1:09:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So I would teach them to move from the weak masculine\Nto the strong masculine, which loves women, sees their beauty,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.81,1:09:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,their intrinsic value and worth, that they nurture life,\Nand honor that which nurtures life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.29,1:09:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that way, you would move from the bottom to that which is,,\Nuplifting, to nurture life.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.21,1:09:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they begin to appreciate and honor women, not as sex\Nfigures, to dance around for erotic entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.57,1:09:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,but for the value of that which they contribute to human life,\Nwhere would you be without the woman?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.99,1:09:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't be born yet.\NI see.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.39,1:09:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The results are coming out in your next book,\Nthe study of the abusing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.13,1:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So the guy who despises women, he says, without woman,\Nyou wouldn't even be here to complain
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.59,1:09:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,about women, young man, you know?\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.59,1:09:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Appreciate that.\NOut of the womb comes men, W-O-M-E-N.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.78,1:10:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You have 15 minutes to do five people.\NYes, we have plenty of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.40,1:10:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,First, I'd like to say I appreciate that you're here.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.14,1:10:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And my question is about fluctuation\Nin consciousness levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.44,1:10:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how else to, I'll use an analogy.\NBecause you say that if someone reads your book,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.12,1:10:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I imagine any of the books, it's transformative.\NFor example, The Power Versus Force,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.88,1:10:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you're, you know, the average consciousness level\Nis at 35 points that it increases.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.34,1:10:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's say someone reads that book,\Nand then they go about their business.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.82,1:10:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They watch 70,000 hours of reality TV shows.\NMaybe they steal a burger from Burger King.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.98,1:10:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Does their, just, you know, I'll just throw that out there,\Nbut does their consciousness level fluctuate?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.26,1:10:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a decrease?\NYes, because you always have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.28,1:10:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant, the mind is making a choice.\NEvery instant.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.78,1:10:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Every instant.\NIf you look at every instant, every instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.90,1:10:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is automatically making a choice.\NWhich way to go?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.58,1:11:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a little hummingbird, you know?\NThis flower, this flower, this flower, this flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.34,1:11:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's constantly going like so.\NSo you can watch consciousness as it flicks,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.74,1:11:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,making its choices, you know, to that which it is attracted,\Nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.09,1:11:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, that which you esteem is that which you are,\Nattracted to, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.27,1:11:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So like I was telling you the last gentleman,\Nthat which you esteem, you're attracted in that direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.33,1:11:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you esteem women, then you honor them.\NAnd if you, you know, otherwise you disgrace them, so.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:34.03,1:11:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if I could just add to that a little.\NIf that's so, and I imagine, of course,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.43,1:11:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,someone wouldn't steal a Whopper, probably,\Nif they were going to read Power Versus Force, but.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.67,1:11:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone would?\NWouldn't steal a burger, I would imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.15,1:11:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, steal a burger.\NYes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.83,1:11:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat if they were hungry?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.18,1:11:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they may, OK.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.42,1:11:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Steal a burger.\NWe could start a bunch of shops called Steal a Burger.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.46,1:11:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Steal a burger.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.94,1:12:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Put a dollar in here, and you get to steal anyone there,\Nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.78,1:12:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's say, you know, there are days where sometimes someone\Nmight feel more connected to source, or to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.48,1:12:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever you want to call it.\NAnd then there are other days where they just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.54,1:12:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,you just, you don't feel that so much.\NYes, yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.14,1:12:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that a, is that symptomatic of,\Nyou know, a consciousness level that has decreased,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.93,1:12:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and that one day it was higher?\NNo, no, no, it's just a hummingbird, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.95,1:12:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the choices are within a certain limitation.\NYou know, you're not choosing to stab somebody to death today.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.49,1:12:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they're still only within a mild range.\NAnd then as your consciousness level moves,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.81,1:12:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,your range moves up to a different level, see?\NThe little bug with his legs waving in the air is only going
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.53,1:12:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to bother you at a certain level.\NBelow that level.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.80,1:12:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Below that level, you're not even going to see it.\NThen in this level, you're going to get caught in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.94,1:13:03.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Then this, beyond this level, you see, you know,\Nyou transcend all of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.30,1:13:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes no difference whether you give it a twig\Nor not to give it a twig.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.86,1:13:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So, so let's say someone's at 510 today.\NA month from now, they can't be at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.16,1:13:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that?\NWell, they could be.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.30,1:13:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is possible.\NYeah, we did, the fellow sawed his arm off
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.36,1:13:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,during the intermission.\NHe was on TV last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.20,1:13:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The story, wasn't it?\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.56,1:13:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The mountain climber who fell into a crevasse,\Nand a big rock imprisoned his arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.05,1:13:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the rock fell on his arm, he calibrated,\Nwe have permission, OK, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.39,1:13:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to share this with the audience, yes?\NThe privacy of the audience, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.82,1:13:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he calibrated at 250.\NTo go mountain climbing, you've really got to be around 250.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.92,1:14:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The rock fell on him, and the level at which he\Nsawed off his arm was 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.38,1:14:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He realized he had to saw off his arm.\NSomehow he energized the divine energy of God, the courage,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.64,1:14:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and he jumped to 505.\NAt the time he sawed off his arm, he calibrated at 505.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.20,1:14:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He has since evolved even further to 510, 510, 515.\NHe's over 510, 515.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.81,1:14:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's over 510 already.\NSo he jumped from 250 to 510.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.69,1:14:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinarily, that would take you about 500 lifetimes.\NHe did it in one lifetime in a matter of days.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.42,1:14:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And he's written a book on it.\NAnd of course, it's quite a story of valor and courage,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.20,1:14:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and very interesting.\NHowever, few of us would be willing to saw off our arm
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.62,1:15:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to jump from 250 to 510.\NAgreed.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.20,1:15:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you do handshakes?\NI do handshakes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.92,1:15:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.95,1:15:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we all salute that young man's courage.\NReally quite something.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.61,1:15:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You had mentioned in your book that there are six or seven\Npeople that have reached a level of 600 in the world right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:24.33,1:15:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that correct?\NI think so.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.25,1:15:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are they?\NOh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:28.41,1:15:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's anonymous.\NAre you one of them?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.41,1:15:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't want to be bothered with your mail.\NI'll keep looking then.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.08,1:15:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt fluctuates, because they sometimes come out,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:45.18,1:15:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and then they topple over.\NThey arrive, and then they leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.05,1:15:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then some crash, too.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.91,1:16:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you talk about dreams from sleeping?\NAre they purely a result of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.91,1:16:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and where the ego is at that time in consciousness?\NOr is it something more?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.03,1:16:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't done the amount of research\NI'd like to do on dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.41,1:16:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've gotten that it's mainly brain physiology that's\Ngoing on, that it's mainly brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:17.89,1:16:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A dream is mainly, primarily brain physiology.\NYeah, it's pretty much brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.61,1:16:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote a critique of Freud's interpretation of dreams\Nmany years ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.71,1:16:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And to me, the dream was a production of the brain,\Na story, and then the story acts like a Rorschach card.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.67,1:16:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you associate it with the brain,\Nwhen you lie on the couch and pre-associate to the dream,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.17,1:16:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it's really like it's a Rorschach card.\NAnd you project into the Rorschach card
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.81,1:16:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is meaningful to you.\NAnd dreams are very profoundly informative in psychoanalysis.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.25,1:17:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember when I transcended the edible complex,\Nand it came as a horrific case of terror.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.63,1:17:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I went in to see my analyst one time, and I lay on the couch.\NI had such an anxiety attack.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.79,1:17:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anxiety.\NAnxiety was getting worse and worse by the weeks.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.15,1:17:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The worse the anxiety got, I couldn't drive over the bridge.\NI couldn't drive through a tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.67,1:17:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I had claustrophobia.\NAnd my analyst was very pleased.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.18,1:17:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was pleased at the great progress.\NSo one day, I go to lay on the analyst.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.38,1:17:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I lay on the couch, and I had an acute anxiety attack,\Nthe great granddaddy of all anxiety attacks,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.38,1:17:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,an absolute terror.\NAnd he said, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.89,1:17:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told him the dream.\NI said, this lion.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.39,1:17:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all by myself, and there's some woman in the background,\Nand this lion attacks me and kills me.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.19,1:17:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, what does that make you think of?\NI said, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.87,1:18:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My mind went blank.\NHe said, do you know any lions?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.37,1:18:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, I don't know any lions.\NHe said, what's my name?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.65,1:18:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, Lionel Obesee, my psychoanalyst\Nwas the father figure, who was going to kill him, castrate,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:14.72,1:18:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,me, because I had a fantasy about stealing his wife\Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.96,1:18:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it came out of the unconscious, for sure.\NAnd I'll tell you, the anxiety attack was real.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.08,1:18:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And his name was Lionel Obesee.\NAnd it was a lion that came to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.08,1:18:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the brain is gone.\NThen once I went through that dream,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.80,1:18:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the analysis of that dream, the edible conflicts and all\Nof it disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.92,1:18:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Since that time, I've had no conflict with men\Nor competition with men.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.04,1:18:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Or power, concerns about power, et cetera.\NSo the psychoanalysis was complete and total
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.50,1:18:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and successful.\NBut it came as a crashing climax to a dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.50,1:19:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So you were asking about dreams.\NI'm telling you what my personal experience is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:00.12,1:19:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,OK?\NOK, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.14,1:19:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than theory, I'm telling you.\NWe have five minutes and a half.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.36,1:19:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That is fine.\NWe are just going to be finishing up perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.02,1:19:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be real quick.\NYes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.50,1:19:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband and I are big students\Nof all your work, as well as Course in Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.28,1:19:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to Toronto a couple of months ago to see you.\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.64,1:19:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we drove down here.\NAnd we're wondering, what can we do to get you
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.02,1:19:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to come to Ann Arbor, Michigan?\NAnn Arbor, Michigan?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.44,1:19:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we're coming in next year.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.04,1:19:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we're scheduled for Michigan, yes.\NWe have a schedule for Michigan next year, but I can't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.38,1:19:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to ask.\NI haven't been to Michigan in so many years.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.94,1:19:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I grew up in Wisconsin, and we used to take the Clipper across\Nto Muskegon, and the family owned a little cottage
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.53,1:19:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,up in Iron Mountain, Michigan.\NAnd I haven't been in there, been to Michigan in 50 years,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.97,1:20:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,probably, so I would enjoy it.\NWell, we would love to have you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.79,1:20:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Thank you.\NAnd can I have a hug?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:04.39,1:20:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have a hug.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.60,1:20:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Kiki.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.28,1:20:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going to do in Michigan?\NThere's a couple we have already.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.74,1:20:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWas it Ann Arbor?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.34,1:20:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Bearers used to, we had a cottage up there\Nand when you went out around the garbage can,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.36,1:20:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you had to chase the Bearers away.\NYou were speaking earlier of intention and forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.38,1:20:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and karma.\NI'd like to ask you if we utilize our intention
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.79,1:20:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to use forgiveness or to invoke forgiveness for ourselves\Nand for other people to work through karma,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.19,1:20:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is that an effective tool for doing that?\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.07,1:21:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you do?\NWell, I mean, in the sense of can it dissolve,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.36,1:21:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that's not the word I'm looking for,\Ncan it neutralize that negative karma or that type of karma
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.06,1:21:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that's making up for it?\NOh, yes, because otherwise nobody would ever
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.12,1:21:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,be able to evolve spiritually.\NSo you take responsibility, you ask for forgiveness,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.36,1:21:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and you choose the positive.\NAnd you use prayer, you ask God's help.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.18,1:21:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think I like what they teach in the Course of Miracles,\Nis what you're really asking is the Holy Spirit
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.42,1:21:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to recontextualize the thing so that you can see it differently.\NWhen you ask for a miracle, what you're saying is,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.52,1:21:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I'm seeing it is limited.\NI ask God to show me the total picture.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.70,1:21:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see the total picture, you realize there's nothing\Nto forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.58,1:21:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only by seeing it is limited, see?\NWhen the lens expands, you see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.86,1:21:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,For one thing, you see that everybody\Nis in a development over time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.84,1:22:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So when you look at content only,\Nyou're taking it outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.90,1:22:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you see the whole picture,\Nyou see the development.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.86,1:22:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And now over time, permanently, it all makes sense.\NAnd you say, so what?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.20,1:22:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't necessarily alleviate life lessons\Nor the type of learning.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.40,1:22:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it gives you an explanation by completing the picture.\NAnd when you see the complete picture,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:17.54,1:22:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize there's nothing to forgive.\NIt gives us a chance to recontextualize.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.62,1:22:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NOK.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:21.66,1:22:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.16,1:22:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's say the third one.\NFirst one.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:32.50,1:22:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, my name's Diane.\NI came from Michigan to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.02,1:22:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to thank you for coming.\NIt's been so inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.70,1:22:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And I wanted to thank Susan, because just watching her\Nand her love and devotion is just inspiring.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.52,1:22:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I also wanted to know when your next book\Nwas coming out.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.98,1:22:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, soon.\NWould it be in my lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:57.80,1:23:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it'll be in your lifetime.\NI hope by the end of the year.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.40,1:23:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I've had to write it and rewrite it and rewrite it.\NI'll tell you what the difficulty is.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:07.52,1:23:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our world has become so contentious\Nthat you can't mention any subject
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.78,1:23:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,without bringing up all kinds of energy about it.\NSo then you say, well, I can express it differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.06,1:23:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can't express anything\Nthat there isn't a parade about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.56,1:23:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So how are you going to tell people the truth of things\Nwithin the world when they all have
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.02,1:23:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a vested positionality about it?\NPeople don't ask what is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.83,1:23:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What they want you to do is to validate what they believe.\NI'm working on that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.27,1:23:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And then lastly, when you leave this body, when you come back.\NOh, I left already.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.59,1:24:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I came back today just for you folks here.\NAnd we're so grateful.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.95,1:24:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAnd thank you in this regard.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.38,1:24:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, thank you so much.\NI love you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.36,1:24:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you all, devotively.\NTo thee, O God, do I surrender my life, my beingness,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:30.35,1:24:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and I open myself to the revelation of the divinity\Nof thy presence as the source of my existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.41,1:24:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Your life becomes the position, the prayer, the supplication,\Nthe surrender, because you are the field and not
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.79,1:24:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the content of the field.\NYou become one with the field, which cannot resist
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.33,1:25:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the mudra of the question, because that which\Nis being asked is the very source of your existence
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.41,1:25:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore cannot refuse.
